# TASK 5: Preserve Material Colors in Renderer

## CONTEXT
Currently loadMesh() overwrites all materials with accent blue. We need to preserve source colors for per-feature coloring.

## CURRENT BEHAVIOR (renderer.js ~line 320)
```javascript
const accentMaterial = new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({
  color: 0x4a9eff,
  side: THREE.DoubleSide
});
loadedMesh.traverse((child) => {
  if (child.isMesh) {
    child.material = accentMaterial; // Overwrites everything!
  }
});
```

## REQUIRED BEHAVIOR
1. Check if mesh already has a non-default material color
2. If source has color info, preserve it
3. If source has no color (default grey), apply accent blue
4. Always set DoubleSide for proper rendering
5. Still add edge lines to all meshes

## IMPLEMENTATION
```javascript
loadedMesh.traverse((child) => {
  if (child.isMesh) {
    // Check if material has a meaningful color (not default grey)
    const hasSourceColor = child.material && 
      child.material.color && 
      !child.material.color.equals(new THREE.Color(0x808080));

    if (hasSourceColor) {
      // Preserve source color, just ensure DoubleSide
      child.material.side = THREE.DoubleSide;
    } else {
      // Apply default accent color
      child.material = new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({
        color: 0x4a9eff,
        side: THREE.DoubleSide
      });
    }
    // Add edge lines...
  }
});
```

## FILES TO MODIFY
- src/renderer/renderer.js

## EXPECTED RESULT
1. If glTF has colored meshes, colors are preserved
2. If glTF has default grey meshes, they get accent blue
3. Edge lines still appear on all meshes

