# TASK 8: Per-Feature Hover Highlight

## CONTEXT
When hovering over a feature, highlight just that feature (not the whole model) with a lighter shade of its current color.

## CURRENT BEHAVIOR
Hover highlights the entire model with blue emissive glow.

## REQUIRED BEHAVIOR
1. Hover highlights only the specific mesh under cursor
2. Highlight effect: lighten the current color (not blue glow)
3. Store original color, restore on mouse leave
4. Throttled at 30fps (already implemented)

## HIGHLIGHT EFFECT
```javascript
function lightenColor(color, amount = 0.3) {
  const hsl = {};
  color.getHSL(hsl);
  hsl.l = Math.min(1, hsl.l + amount);
  return new THREE.Color().setHSL(hsl.h, hsl.s, hsl.l);
}

function applyFeatureHighlight(mesh) {
  mesh.userData.originalColor = mesh.material.color.clone();
  mesh.material.color.copy(lightenColor(mesh.userData.originalColor));
}

function removeFeatureHighlight(mesh) {
  if (mesh.userData.originalColor) {
    mesh.material.color.copy(mesh.userData.originalColor);
    delete mesh.userData.originalColor;
  }
}
```

## FILES TO MODIFY
- src/renderer/renderer.js (update hover system)

## EXPECTED RESULT
1. Load multi-body model with different colored features
2. Hover over one feature -> only that feature lightens
3. Move to another feature -> first returns to normal, second lightens
4. Move off model -> all normal colors

