# TASK 10: Apply Color and Log to Chat

## CONTEXT
When user selects a color from palette, apply it to the feature and log the change to chat.

## REQUIREMENTS
1. On color selection:
   - Apply color to selected feature's material
   - Add message to chat: "Color of Feature [N] changed to [color name]"
   - Mark project as dirty (unsaved changes)
2. Color names for chat message:
   - #000000 -> "black"
   - #ffffff -> "white"
   - #4a9eff -> "blue"
   - #ff4444 -> "red"
   - #ffff00 -> "yellow"
   - #44ff44 -> "green"
   - #00ffff -> "cyan"
   - #ff00ff -> "magenta"
   - #ff9900 -> "orange"
3. Store color overrides for save/load (next task)

## IMPLEMENTATION
```javascript
const colorNames = {
  0x000000: 'black',
  0xffffff: 'white',
  // ...
};

function applyFeatureColor(feature, colorHex) {
  feature.material.color.setHex(colorHex);

  const colorName = colorNames[colorHex] || 'custom';
  const featureNum = feature.userData.featureIndex;

  // Add to chat as system message (not user/assistant)
  addMessage('system', `Color of Feature ${featureNum} changed to ${colorName}`);

  // Mark dirty
  isDirty = true;
  updateWindowTitle();

  // Store override
  featureColors[featureNum] = colorHex;
}
```

