# TASK 14: Render Mode Selector

## CONTEXT
Users should be able to switch between Solid, Wireframe, and X-Ray render modes.

## RENDER MODES
1. **Solid** (default): Normal shaded view with edge lines
2. **Wireframe**: Only edge lines visible, faces transparent
3. **X-Ray**: Semi-transparent faces with visible edge lines

## REQUIREMENTS
1. Add render mode dropdown or button group to toolbar
2. Default: Solid
3. Switching mode updates all meshes in currentMesh
4. Mode persists until changed

## IMPLEMENTATION
```javascript
let renderMode = 'solid'; // 'solid' | 'wireframe' | 'xray'

function setRenderMode(mode) {
  renderMode = mode;
  if (!currentMesh) return;

  currentMesh.traverse((child) => {
    if (child.isMesh) {
      switch (mode) {
        case 'solid':
          child.material.wireframe = false;
          child.material.transparent = false;
          child.material.opacity = 1;
          child.visible = true;
          break;
        case 'wireframe':
          child.material.wireframe = true;
          // Or: hide mesh, show only edge lines
          break;
        case 'xray':
          child.material.wireframe = false;
          child.material.transparent = true;
          child.material.opacity = 0.3;
          break;
      }
    }
  });
}
```

