# TASK 15: Fit to View Button

## CONTEXT
Users should be able to reset the camera to frame the entire model.

## REQUIREMENTS
1. Add Fit to View button to toolbar (icon: frame/zoom-to-fit)
2. Clicking calls fitCameraToObject with current mesh
3. Uses current view direction (doesn't reset to isometric)
4. Works even after user has orbited/zoomed away
5. Optional: keyboard shortcut (F key)

## IMPLEMENTATION
```javascript
function fitToView() {
  const target = currentMesh || testCube;
  if (target) {
    // Get current camera direction
    const direction = new THREE.Vector3();
    camera.getWorldDirection(direction);
    direction.negate(); // Camera looks opposite to its direction

    fitCameraToObject(target, direction);
  }
}
```

Or simpler - just use isometric view:
```javascript
function fitToView() {
  const target = currentMesh || testCube;
  if (target) {
    fitCameraToObject(target, viewPresets.isometric);
  }
}
```

## FILES TO MODIFY
- src/renderer/index.html (add button)
- src/renderer/renderer.js (fit logic)

## EXPECTED RESULT
1. Load a model
2. Zoom way in or orbit away
3. Click Fit to View
4. Camera resets to show entire model

Provide a plan before implementing code.
